Singapore Finance Minister Sees ‘Tough’ Years Ahead, Times Says

-- B y   C h a n y a p o r n   C h a n j a r o e n
-- 
2011-08-07T01:14:54Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-07/singapore-finance-minister-sees-tough-years-ahead-times-says.html
Singapore ’s Finance Minister Tharman Shanmugaratnam expects the next three to four years to be
“tough” as a global economic slowdown affects the city-state,
the Sunday Times reported.  There is a crisis of confidence in the U.S.,  Europe  and
 Japan , Shanmugaratnam, also deputy prime minister, said in a
speech yesterday according to the paper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Chanyaporn Chanjaroen in Singapore at 
 cchanjaroen@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Paul Tighe at   ptighe@bloomberg.net . 